      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Nationalism is a complex ideology with both positive and negative potential. When it fosters civic pride, shared identity, and collective action for the common good, it can promote social cohesion. However, when it devolves into chauvinism, xenophobia, and the belief in inherent national superiority, it becomes a dangerously divisive force. Therefore, its impact depends heavily on how it is defined and practiced within a society.",
