    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a pretty heavy way to put it. so you're saying the \"danger\" side is basically the more factual or realistic take based on history? if history just shows it ends in \"us vs them\" or oppression, isn't it kind of misleading to even present the \"social cohesion\" side as an equal possibility? it feels like you're saying the good version is just a theory and the bad version is the reality.",
